<p>
    <b>ContentTools</b> aims to provide both a fully-functional content editor that can be used out of the box and a tool kit of classes and functions that can be used to build your own editor. The tool kit includes a lightweight set of user interface classes, a set of tools for performing common editing tasks, and a history stack for managing undo/redo. Whilst the components provided by the tool kit work well together, they can also be used or replaced as required.
</p>
<p>
    The rest of this page is purely reference documentation for the <b>ContentTools</b> library, for usage guides and examples I recommend you read the <a href="/getting-started">Getting Started</a> guide and other <a href="/tutorials">Tutorials</a>.
</p>
